Hello: I hope this doesn't seem like I'm splitting hairs, but the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) does not apply to the Federal government. 
Agencies of the Federal government are covered under Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973. 
Section 504 does contain requirements for communication access similar to those found in Title II of the ADA. 
