Hi Mike, No it doesn't sound like splitting hairs. 
However, the US Federal Government is very clearly covered by Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act, which applies to all Information Technology (IT) procurement by the Federal Government, and, by extension through the "Tech Act," Section 508 applies to State Government IT procurement as well. 
So there is no lack of obligation in the US for Federal &amp; State entities to have their Web sites accessible. 
Robert, since Mike Muehe's message as well as yours went to the large cc field, you may want to follow up with those folks -- separately from this list please -- to provide further clarification as needed. 
Regards, Judy 
